gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 114, Celtics 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Celtics, 114-105. Austin Reaves recorded a season-high 32 points and a career-high seven 3PM for the Lakers, with DAngelo Russell adding 16 points, a season-high 14 assists, and eight rebounds in the victory. Jayson Tatum tallied 23 points, seven rebounds, and three assists for the Celtics in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 25-25, while the Celtics fall to 37-12.
